---
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/blog-placeholder-about.jpg';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About Me"
	description="Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet"
	pubDate={new Date('August 08 2021')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
<body>

	<main>
		<section class="hero">

			<p>
				Hey, I’m Manubhav Sharma — a Computer Science (AI) student,
				builder, and someone who enjoys figuring out how things work
				under the hood.
			</p>

			<p>
				I enjoy building projects that sit at the intersection of
				artificial intelligence, software engineering, and practical
				problem solving.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>My Journey Into Tech</h2>

			<p>
				What started as curiosity slowly turned into an obsession with
				building things. Over time, that curiosity evolved into working on
				AI systems, full-stack applications, mobile apps, testing workflows,
				and experimenting with different technologies.
			</p>

			<p>
				I enjoy learning by building — which means most concepts I learn
				eventually become projects, notes, experiments, or blog posts.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>Things I Like Working On</h2>

			<ul>
				<li>Artificial Intelligence & Deep Learning</li>
				<li>System Design & Architecture</li>
				<li>Full Stack Development</li>
				<li>Developer Productivity Systems</li>
				<li>Performance Optimization</li>
				<li>Problem Solving & Algorithms</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>Projects & Experiments</h2>

			<p>
				I enjoy building projects that solve practical problems and teach
				me something new in the process.
			</p>

			<ul>
				<li>AI-powered FIR Classification System</li>
				<li>Collaborative Team Management Platform</li>
				<li>Bluetooth Data Streaming Application</li>
				<li>Expense Tracking Platform</li>
				<li>Various experiments in AI and automation</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>Why I Write</h2>

			<p>
				This blog exists because writing helps me think better.
			</p>

			<p>
				Here, I document concepts, mistakes, debugging sessions,
				project decisions, and things I wish someone had explained
				to me earlier.
			</p>

			<p>
				If you're also learning, building, or experimenting —
				hopefully something here helps.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>Beyond Code</h2>

			<p>
				Apart from coding, I enjoy problem solving, logic building,
				competitive challenges, and exploring how technology can
				make systems more efficient.
			</p>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>
